On the opposite side, the raised area around the pierced hole is 1.7cm in diameter, and at least 0.5cm high (but is broken). The side with the broken raised area around the hole also has an incised decoration of varialby 0.4cm long, ~0.1cm deep lines arranged in a swirl; that is the lines extend diagonally from the raised area to the edge of the object. Similar lines occur on the sides of the raised area, but these lines are more vertical than oblique. Under 10X magnification, incised lines appear to have been made with a thin twig or reed. Munsell: body: 10YR 6/3 Pale Brown on unbroken side; Grades to 10YR 5/1 gray on rchipped aised area. Core is also 10YR 5/1 Gray.weight 9g; 3.2cm at widest; preserved height (is broken) 1.5cm. small ceramic weaving implement (more likely) or miniature wagon wheel (less likely?); hand-formed bi-conical disk with greater diameter at mid-section; tapers to funnel-shaped tips creating an 'axel' like shape with a hole punched laterally through the center. The wobbly surface, especially on the outer edge around the circumference, shows wear; parts of the edge are flattened and lighter in color than the conical 'faces' of the object. NB: THIS OBJECT WAS PUBLISHED IN THE 2001 SMALL FINDS REPORT AS H1.1003.1012 "A small ceramic wheel (KT1012) was recovered from trench H1, Locus 1003. This crudely formed 6.3g wheel measures 19mm in diameter with funnel-shaped sides forming an axle measuring 22mm wide. The very pale brown (Munsell 10YR 7/4) wobbly surface has a highly visible chaff temper. The outer edge around the circumference shows wear; parts of the edge are flattened and lighter in color than the faces of the wheel." THIS OBJECT WAS ASSIGNED SAME KT AS BAG OF POTTERY; UNCLEAR WHETHER THIS SMALL FIND WAS PULLED FROM POTTERY READING (UNLIKELY). MORE LIKELY THAT OBJECT CAME TO DIGHOUSE AS A SEPARATE OBJECT. NONETHELESS, THE DUPLICATE KT PROBLEM WAS FIXED BY ASSIGNING NEW KT H1.1003.1 TO THIS SMALL FIND. exterior: 10YR 7/4 very pale brown exterior has highly visible chaff temper NB: fabric not readable w/o damaging object
